            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "This would be great. \n\nFor what it's worth, `lazy.nvim` uses [vim.secure.read to load .lazy.lua](https://github.com/folke/lazy.nvim/blob/306a05526ada86a7b30af95c5cc81ffba93fef97/lua/lazy/core/plugin.lua#L295-L306) files to support modifying your package `spec`'s, and you could configure your plugin to be disabled that way (explicitly adding the plugin spec in your `.lazy.lua` with `enabled = false`). I only mention this because it might simplify your current approach @schilkp . \n\nI'd still love to see the ability to do more \"greedy\" exrc loading, as then I could set some `vim.g` variables and use them in my lazy plugin specs, etc, and wouldn't need a `.lazy.lua`.\n\n",
