        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I would be opposed to changing the default behavior of `exrc`.\n\n> - Make `exrc` greedy, triggering the sourcing as soon as it is set\n\nThis is a really janky way to fix this niche issue. It requires all configs to adapt their structure to this option (for example, in my config, I set all of my options first), and as noted, a user has to be incredibly careful on the ordering of there config for this to work at all.\n\n> - Introduce a separate option to make `exrc` greedy or not, which can default to off to stay compatible with Vim.\n> - Make `exrc` accept multiple possible values?\n\nI'm not sold on the actual use of this as a feature. For one, you still need to set `exrc=greedy` or `greedyexrc` in your config, which breaks the system anyway as it could only work if the option was somehow set *before* the config loads.\n\n---\n\nAdditionally, the usecase you describe could be simplified by enabling the plugin on `VimEnter` as long as a certain `g:dont_load_X_plugin` variable is not set by `exrc`.\n\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('VimEnter', {\n  callback = function()\n    if vim.g.dont_load_lspconfig_plugin ~= 1 then\n      vim.pack.add('https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig')\n    end\n  end,\n})",
            "created_at": "2026-03-19T08:06:53Z",
